      • createPlot

        public Plot createPlot()
        Create a plot with the initial values.
        • cacheable: true
        • color: BLACK
        • font: Serif PLAIN 12
        • margin: extra 12 on left, top, right, bottom
        • sizeMode: FillContainerSizeMode(1)
        • containerSize: 640x480
          Returns:
          a plot

        • createSubplot

          public Plot createSubplot()
          Create a plot which can be added as a subplot of another plot. A subplot is same as a plot, except its size are managed by the layout director of its parent plot.

          the initial values

          • cacheable: false
          • color: unassigned, means inherit from its parent plot
          • font: unassigned, means inherit from its parent plot
          • margin: no extra margin
          • sizeMode: unassigned
          • containerSize: unassigned
            Returns:
            a plot

          • createAxes

            public PlotAxis[] createAxes(int n)
            Create n Axes which share the same tick manager. The position of the axis on index 0 is AxisPosition.NEGATIVE_SIDE, the position of the axis on index 1 is AxisPosition.POSITIVE_SIDE. All the created axes must be added to a plot by Plot.addXAxes(PlotAxis[]) or Plot.addYAxes(PlotAxis[])
            Returns:
            axes in an array
